now for the mail server,

00:42:49.770 --> 00:42:52.980
where we allow you to set up
multiple virtual mail domains.

00:42:53.000 --> 00:42:57.240
So if you have, for instance,
Company 1 and Company 2 on your server,

00:42:57.320 --> 00:43:02.260
you can have the same mail name,
sales@company1 or sales@company2,

00:43:02.260 --> 00:43:05.150
go to multiple independent
mailboxes on the server.

00:43:05.220 --> 00:43:07.700
We've enhanced the
support for mail quotas,

00:43:07.700 --> 00:43:11.640
so you can have soft quotas with
customizable messages as well as hard

00:43:11.770 --> 00:43:16.290
quotas that will actually stop delivery
of mail to mailboxes that are full.

00:43:16.480 --> 00:43:19.240
We've also delivered some
enhancements to QuickTime streaming.

00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:23.100
We've enhanced the QTS publisher
for improved workflow and

00:43:23.100 --> 00:43:24.900
added AppleScript support.

00:43:24.970 --> 00:43:28.830
And we've enhanced the scalability
of QuickTime streaming to support bit

00:43:28.830 --> 00:43:35.720
rates that can now deliver HD quality on
local intranets with our latest codecs.

00:43:37.080 --> 00:43:40.240
That's internet services in Tiger Server.

00:43:40.380 --> 00:43:42.550
And lastly,
another area that you've heard

00:43:42.680 --> 00:43:45.590
in the previous sessions a bit
about today is high performance

00:43:45.610 --> 00:43:48.340
computing with grid clusters.

00:43:48.420 --> 00:43:53.240
And we have previously released
a technology preview of a

00:43:53.310 --> 00:43:55.060
technology we call X Grid.

00:43:55.150 --> 00:43:59.020
And we're improving that and
productizing that in Tiger Server.

00:43:59.110 --> 00:44:03.050
X Grid will provide software that
you need to provide clustering

00:44:03.050 --> 00:44:05.020
in Mac OS X and Mac OS X Server.

00:44:05.100 --> 00:44:09.680
You can do that through a dedicated
set of XServe clustering nodes.

00:44:09.740 --> 00:44:14.070
Or you can also use X Grid to harvest
spare CPU cycles from desktops that

00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:18.530
you have in your network when they're
not being used for ad hoc clustering.

00:44:18.600 --> 00:44:23.330
X Grid will have an SDK that allows
you to embed awareness and use of

00:44:23.330 --> 00:44:25.760
the grid into your applications.

00:44:26.150 --> 00:44:29.850
It also works with command line
applications so that you can distribute

00:44:29.980 --> 00:44:34.820
command line jobs that have no inherent
awareness of the grid or the cluster.

00:44:34.890 --> 00:44:38.200
We provide management tools that
let you set up the grid through

00:44:38.200 --> 00:44:40.280
server admin and manage your systems.

00:44:40.330 --> 00:44:43.530
And you can manage jobs and
job submission and node status

00:44:43.530 --> 00:44:45.520
from any client on the network.

00:44:45.640 --> 00:44:48.120
And like all of the other
services in Tiger Server,

00:44:48.230 --> 00:44:51.680
it's integrated with
Open Directory for security.

00:44:52.790 --> 00:44:57.010
So those are the services layer in
Tegra Server in Mac OS X Server.

00:44:57.080 --> 00:44:59.640
Server administration,
directory services, workgroup,

00:44:59.830 --> 00:45:04.210
client management, internet,
and high performance computing.

